cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of an efficient vehicular communication platform.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of real-time pervasive information collection and big data processing.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of data analytics techniques to provide intelligent transportation services.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of recommender systems for access decisions.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the use of a distributed automatic access engine.
